cs.NI, cs.MA, cs.SI, cs.IT, cs.PF 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on analyzing the impact of mobility on network performance in cellular networks, which falls under the domain of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) - The paper proposes a random waypoint mobility model and applies it to analyze cellular network parameters, which can be considered as a multiagent system. 
3. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper deals with analyzing the stochastic properties of different mobility models and their impact on network performance, which can be related to social and information networks. 
4. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper presents analytic expressions for handover rate and sojourn time, which can be considered as information theoretic measures. 
5. cs.PF (Performance) - The paper aims to understand the fundamentals of mobility in cellular networks and analyze its impact on network performance, which falls under the domain of performance evaluation.
